>>> Code & Scripts:

1. Import Required Libraries : Essential Python modules used in the project: 
import cv2 
import numpy as np 
import serial 
import time 
import tflite_runtime.interpreter as tflite

2. Initialize Camera : Camera configured for 320x240 resolution with auto-exposure disabled for better frame consistency: 
cap = cv2.VideoCapture(0) 
cap.set(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_WIDTH, 320) 
cap.set(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_HEIGHT, 240) 

3. Load TensorFlow Lite Model : Load and allocate tensors for YOLOv5n or SSD TFLite model: 
interpreter = tflite.Interpreter(model_path="model.tflite") 
interpreter.allocate_tensors() 
input_details = interpreter.get_input_details() 
output_details = interpreter.get_output_details()

4. Frame Preprocessing : Captured frame is resized and normalized before feeding into the model: 
ret, frame = cap.read() 
frame_resized = cv2.resize(frame, (input_width, input_height)) 
input_data = np.expand_dims(frame_resized / 255.0, axis=0).astype(np.float32)

5. Inference and Bounding Box Extraction : Run inference and retrieve object coordinates: 
interpreter.set_tensor(input_details[0]['index'], input_data) 
interpreter.invoke() 
output_data = interpreter.get_tensor(output_details[0]['index']) 
# Post-processing logic to extract box, label, confidence

6. Calculate Object Position : Compare object center to frame center to derive control intent: 
object_x = (box[0] + box[2]) / 2 
frame_center = frame.shape[1] / 2 
offset = object_x - frame_center

7. Send Control Signal via UART : Depending on offset, send yaw/roll commands to flight controller: 
if offset > 50: 
command = "YAW_RIGHT" 
elif offset < -50: 
command = "YAW_LEFT" 
else: 
command = "HOLD" 
ser.write((command + "\n").encode())

8. Frame Display for Debugging : Overlay bounding boxes and display inference output (if GUI is connected): 
cv2.rectangle(frame, (x1, y1), (x2, y2), (0, 255, 0), 2) 
cv2.imshow("Tracking", frame)


>>> This script loops continuously until interrupted. It enables full realtime object tracking by leveraging edge inference and command-based control.
